---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Tax Bracket Optimizer",
  "description": "Calculate your marginal vs effective tax rates and discover the best places to contribute to lower your overall taxes.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "FireMaths"
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a marginal tax rate?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Your marginal tax rate is the tax rate you pay on the very last dollar you earn. It is the highest bracket your income falls into."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is an effective tax rate?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Your effective tax rate is your overall tax burden expressed as a percentage of your total income. It is always lower than your marginal rate in a progressive tax system."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How can I lower my tax bracket?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "You can lower your tax bracket by increasing deductions. The most common way for FIRE followers is by contributing to pre-tax retirement accounts like a Traditional 401(k), Traditional IRA, or an HSA."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="firemaths"
  title="Tax Bracket Optimizer"
  description="Calculate your marginal vs effective tax rates and discover the best places to contribute to lower your overall taxes."
  canonical="https://firemaths.info/tax-bracket-optimizer"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Tax Bracket Optimizer</h1>
      <p>Visualize your marginal vs effective rate and find optimization opportunities.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>Tax Calculator (2024 Brackets)</h2>

      <div class="calculator-form">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="filingStatus">Filing Status</label>
          <select id="filingStatus">
            <option value="single">Single</option>
            <option value="mfj">Married Filing Jointly</option>
          </select>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="grossIncome">Gross Income</label>
          <div class="input-prefix">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="grossIncome" value="100000" min="0" step="1000" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="deductions">Pre-tax Deductions (401k, HSA, etc.)</label>
          <div class="input-prefix">
            <span>$</span>
            <input type="number" id="deductions" value="0" min="0" step="1000" />
          </div>
        </div>

        <button id="calcBtn" class="calc-btn">Optimize My Taxes</button>
      </div>

      <div class="results" id="results" style="display:none;">
        <div class="results-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">Taxable Income</p>
            <h3 id="resTaxableIncome" style="margin:0; font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary)">$0</h3>
          </div>
          <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">Total Estimated Tax</p>
            <h3 id="resTotalTax" style="margin:0; font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent-color)">$0</h3>
          </div>
          <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">Marginal Tax Rate</p>
            <h3 id="resMarginalRate" style="margin:0; font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-primary)">0%</h3>
          </div>
          <div style="background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); padding: 1rem; border-radius: 8px;">
            <p style="margin:0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary)">Effective Tax Rate</p>
            <h3 id="resEffectiveRate" style="margin:0; font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--accent-color)">0%</h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--text-secondary)">Includes standard deduction for selected filing status. Note: State and FICA taxes not included.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card content-section">
      <h2>Understanding Marginal vs Effective Rates</h2>
      <p>Many people misunderstand the progressive tax system. They think "If I enter the 24% bracket, all my income is taxed at 24%." This is mathematically false.</p>
      <p>In a progressive system, your income fills up "buckets" (brackets). Only the dollars that spill into the highest bucket are taxed at that highest rate. This is your <strong>Marginal Tax Rate</strong>.</p>
      <p>Your <strong>Effective Tax Rate</strong> is your total tax divided by your total income. It is always much lower than your marginal rate.</p>

      <h3>Optimization Strategy for FIRE</h3>
      <p>If your marginal rate is high (e.g., 24% or 32%), every dollar you put into a pre-tax 401(k) or HSA saves you 24 or 32 cents on the dollar right now.</p>
      <p>During early retirement, your income will likely be much lower. When you withdraw those pre-tax funds, they will fill the bottom brackets first (10% and 12%). This arbitrage—saving at 24% and paying at 12% later—is a core strategy detailed in our <a href="/tax-optimization-fire-guide">Tax Optimization FIRE Guide</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const brackets2024 = {
      single: {
        stdDeduction: 14600,
        brackets: [
          { rate: 0.10, max: 11600 },
          { rate: 0.12, max: 47150 },
          { rate: 0.22, max: 100525 },
          { rate: 0.24, max: 191950 },
          { rate: 0.32, max: 243725 },
          { rate: 0.35, max: 609350 },
          { rate: 0.37, max: Infinity }
        ]
      },
      mfj: {
        stdDeduction: 29200,
        brackets: [
          { rate: 0.10, max: 23200 },
          { rate: 0.12, max: 94300 },
          { rate: 0.22, max: 201050 },
          { rate: 0.24, max: 383900 },
          { rate: 0.32, max: 487450 },
          { rate: 0.35, max: 731200 },
          { rate: 0.37, max: Infinity }
        ]
      }
    };

    document.getElementById('calcBtn').addEventListener('click', function() {
      const status = document.getElementById('filingStatus').value;
      const grossIncome = parseFloat(document.getElementById('grossIncome').value) || 0;
      const deductions = parseFloat(document.getElementById('deductions').value) || 0;

      const config = brackets2024[status];
      const taxableIncome = Math.max(0, grossIncome - deductions - config.stdDeduction);

      let tax = 0;
      let marginalRate = 0;
      let previousMax = 0;

      for (const b of config.brackets) {
        if (taxableIncome > previousMax) {
          const taxableInThisBracket = Math.min(taxableIncome, b.max) - previousMax;
          tax += taxableInThisBracket * b.rate;
          marginalRate = b.rate * 100;
        } else {
          break;
        }
        previousMax = b.max;
      }

      const effectiveRate = grossIncome > 0 ? (tax / grossIncome) * 100 : 0;

      document.getElementById('resTaxableIncome').innerText = '$' + taxableIncome.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0});
      document.getElementById('resTotalTax').innerText = '$' + tax.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 0, maximumFractionDigits: 0});
      document.getElementById('resMarginalRate').innerText = marginalRate.toFixed(1) + '%';
      document.getElementById('resEffectiveRate').innerText = effectiveRate.toFixed(2) + '%';

      document.getElementById('results').style.display = 'block';
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    }
    .hero {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .hero p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
    }
    .calculator-form {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .input-group {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .input-prefix {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .input-prefix span {
      padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .input-prefix input, select {
      flex: 1;
      padding: 0.5rem;
      border: none;
      background: transparent;
      color: inherit;
      font-size: 1rem;
      outline: none;
    }
    select {
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: 6px;
      background: #111;
      padding: 0.6rem;
    }
    .calc-btn {
      background: var(--accent-color);
      color: #000;
      border: none;
      padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-weight: bold;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
      transition: opacity 0.2s;
    }
    .calc-btn:hover {
      opacity: 0.9;
    }
    .results {
      padding-top: 1.5rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    }
    .content-section h2, .content-section h3 {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
    }
    .content-section p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    a {
      color: var(--accent-color);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
